---
description: Keep store subscriptions as low as possible to minimize re-renders
alwaysApply: true
---

# React State Encapsulation

- Subscribe to stores (Zustand, etc.) in the leaf component that needs the data.
- Avoid lifting store subscriptions to parent containers—this causes the entire subtree to re-render when the subscribed state changes.
- When a component must be controlled (value/onChange props), consider a thin container that subscribes and passes props down, rather than subscribing in a higher-level parent.
